sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: T7stop
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Raik Gruenberg
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
T7 terminator for protein expression in E. coli or in vitro.
Part is provided in R.F.C. 25 assembly format.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
* taken from pET3a expression plasmid
* added two STOP to 5'
* conservative choice of part boundary, could probably be shortened

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: T7RSR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kaiyin Feng
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: It is a repeat-spacer-repeat region designed according to E.coli's CRISPR/Cas system. It also includes a T7 promoter and T7 terminator. THe spacer is designed to target on a segment of non-coding-sequence in E.coli's genome. This biobrick can be transformed into E.coli cells to hopefully construct a suicide system with E.coli's CRISPR/Cas system.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The repeat-spacer-repeat region design should be consistent with the operating principles of E.coli's CRISPR/cas system.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The 'repeat' sequence in CRISPR/cas system of E.coli strain K12.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K533001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: ZHANG Yunxiao
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This part contains the N-terminal 180 amino acids of OmpA fused to SH3 domain in human Grb2 protein.
The N-terminal of OmpA allows the moiety fused to it to be presented on to the outer membrane of E. Coli.
SH3 domain allows for binding to multi-proline peptide in human cells, which functions as a crucial adaptor module in signaling. In our part, this is specially for binding to the proteins for transportation by E. Coli.
All the coding sequence is under T7 promoter and lac repressor binding site. The parts is most efficiently presented onto the membrane when induced at 0.1mM IPTG at 18 centigrade in BL21 E. Coli strain.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: High expression efficiency as well as inducible expression is most desirable when considering a coding sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: OmpA is derived from the genomic DNA of BL21 (DE3) E. Coli strain while SH3 is from human Grb2.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K921000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Eric Pederson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a mutant T7 promoter that includes a lacO sequence. This is repressible by the LacI protein and is induced in the presence of IPTG. The promoter sits in the 5' region of the gene of interest and initiates transcription when the cell expresses T7 RNA polymerase. Be sure you are using a cell strain that includes this gene (DE3).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There are three portions to the T7 promoter: the recognition site, the melting box (or TATA box) and the initation site. Mutations in these sequences caused differential behavior from the wild type.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The part consists of a sequences that resemble a T7 promoter and the lacO sequence found in E. coli.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K533003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: ZHANG Yunxiao
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: OmpA is used to present HIV aspartyl protease outside the E. Coli membrane so that it can cut other proteins with the specific sequence outside in the media.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Since HIV protease is a dimer, dimerization is a great concern to its function. Function of this protease is tested in BL21.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: HIV protease sequence is from former part BBa_I712667. OmpA sequence is from BL21(DE3) e. Coli strain.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K533002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: ZHANG Yunxiao
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Added HIV protease site between OmpA and SH3 for easier release.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The HIV protease site is embedded in the protein so that a proteolytic cleavage can release the binding cassette.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: OmpA is from BL21(DE3) E. Coli genomic DNA. SH3 is from human Grb2 protein. HIV protease site is from a former part.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1680026
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Katharina Sporbeck
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Expression Plasmid coding for His-tag, also containing a thrombine cleavage site between coding region and Histag, so that His-tag can be cleaved off. Vecotr opening with PstI/XmaI, clone part into it with PstI/NgoMIV. Ampicillin resistance.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: very strong RBS 6xHis-Tag Thromin-cleavage-site NgoMIV-compatible restriction site for in-frame insertion

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1428000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T7 promoter-driven BMC structural genes with a His6-tagged component for purification
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lai Hei Ming
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: T7 promoter diving the expression of His6-tagged EutS, with subsequent Plac-driven EutM, EutN, EutL, EutK
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Clone BBa_K311004 into pET28a via NheI and NdeI

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: T7start
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Raik Gruenberg
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong T7 promoter and RBS including start codon for protein expression in E. coli or in-vitro. Part is provided in RFC 25 assembly format.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
* sequence is taken from the commonly used pET3a expression vector
* deleted XbaI site between prom. and RBS
* T7 promoter sequence (1-19) equals the one in BBa_I712074
* Conservative choice of part boundaries and modifications -- the part's size could probably be reduced.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K559001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jacky, Fong Chuen, Loo
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Halorhodopsin under constitute T7 promoter to regulate the gene transcription to be maximized and no restrict to other regulatory factor
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The coding sequence of N.pharaonis J05199.1 is selected from 61nt to 700nt and the T7 promotor placed in front by 3A assembly
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Halorhodopsin come from N.pharaonis, gene bank J05199.1

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K559010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jacky, Fong Chuen, Loo
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Halorhodopsin gene allow chloride ion to be pumped in by the level of light intensity. Halorhodopsin gene is under regulation by constitute T7 promoter to allow protein coding to be maximized, and the bidirectional terminator is added for high efficiency termination of both forward and backward transcription
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The double terminator wass tested to stop effectively on the transcription of both forward and backward transcription to make our protein generator be a controlled system
